---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Accessibility — M³"
  description="Accessibility statement for M³. We aim to conform to WCAG 2.1 Level AA. Reach us at murillomartinezmichael@gmail.com if any part of the site is not usable for you."
  path="/accessibility"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'M³', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Accessibility', url: '/accessibility' },
  ]}
>
  <Header slot="header" minimal={true} path="/accessibility" />

  <section class="container-page py-16 lg:py-24 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-bone-muted">Statement · Accessibility</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl leading-[1.05] text-bone">
      Accessibility <em class="text-clay italic">Statement</em>
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-bone-muted leading-relaxed">
      M³ is committed to making this website usable by as many people as possible, including people
      with disabilities. This page explains what we are doing and how to reach us if any part of
      the site is not working for you.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-14 font-display text-2xl text-bone">Our commitment</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-bone-muted leading-relaxed">
      We aim to conform to the
      <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-clay underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-bone">
        Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA</a>.
      These guidelines cover readable text, sufficient color contrast, keyboard navigation, alt
      text on meaningful images, and clear labeling — the things that make a site work for people
      using screen readers, screen magnifiers, or keyboard-only navigation.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-14 font-display text-2xl text-bone">What we have done</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 text-bone-muted leading-relaxed list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>A skip-to-content link at the top of every page for keyboard users.</li>
      <li>A single <code class="text-sm bg-ink-panel px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;main&gt;</code> landmark on every page.</li>
      <li>Labeled buttons and form fields — no icon-only controls without an accessible name.</li>
      <li>Visible keyboard focus indicators throughout.</li>
      <li>Full support for <code class="text-sm bg-ink-panel px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">prefers-reduced-motion</code> — animations disable for users who ask for less motion.</li>
      <li>A defined page language (<code class="text-sm bg-ink-panel px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">lang="en"</code>) so screen readers pronounce content correctly.</li>
      <li>ARIA live regions on the intake form so async submission feedback is announced.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-14 font-display text-2xl text-bone">Known limitations</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-bone-muted leading-relaxed">
      Accessibility is ongoing work. If something on the site gets in your way — a page you can't
      navigate, text you can't read, a form that won't accept your input — please tell us. We
      treat accessibility reports as a priority.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-14 rounded-lg border border-ink-line bg-ink-panel/40 p-6 sm:p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-bone">How to contact us</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-bone-muted leading-relaxed">
        If you have trouble using any part of this site, or need information in a different format:
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-bone">
        <strong>Email:</strong>
        <a href="mailto:murillomartinezmichael@gmail.com" class="text-clay underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-bone">murillomartinezmichael@gmail.com</a>
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-bone-muted text-sm">We aim to respond within two business days.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-10 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-bone-muted">Last updated · July 10, 2026</p>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" path="/accessibility" />
</Layout>
